quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  16,35,"The polytheists argue, “Had God willed, neither we nor our forefathers would have worshipped anything other than Him, nor prohibited anything without His command.” So did those before them. Is not the messengers’ duty only to deliver ˹the message˺ clearly"
  16,36,"We surely sent a messenger to every community, saying, “Worship God and shun false gods.” But some of them were guided by God, while others were destined to stray. So travel throughout the land and see the fate of the deniers"
  16,37,"Even though you ˹O Prophet˺ are keen on their guidance, God certainly does not guide those He leaves to stray, and they will have no helpers"
  16,38,"They swear by God their most solemn oaths that God will never raise the dead to life. Yes ˹He will˺! It is a true promise binding on Him, but most people do not know"
  16,39,"˹He will do that˺ to make clear to them what they disagreed on, and for the disbelievers to know that they were liars"
  16,40,"If We ever will something ˹to exist˺, all We say is: “Be!” And it is"
  16,41,"As for those who emigrated in ˹the cause of˺ God after being persecuted, We will surely bless them with a good home in this world. But the reward of the Hereafter is far better, if only they knew"
  16,42,"˹It is˺ they who have patiently endured, and in their Lord they put their trust"